But, if engineers who had concerns witnessing foam debris strike the shuttle's left wing and needed data to examine the shuttle's wing could have informed the Air Force's Recon. SAT surveillance system equipped with NEP/NTP propulsion and power to perform effortless orbit changes without much trouble during the span of Columbia's mission. <br>
